      "title": "UK politician Ann Widdecombe beaten to death in own home",
      "content_html": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/10/uk-politician-ann-widdecombe-beaten-to-death-in-own-home.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"UK politician Ann Widdecombe beaten to death in own home\"><img alt=\"Ann Widdecombe, then Under Secretary of State for Social Security and Conservative M.P. for Maidstone, in 1991. Photo: David Fowler / Shutterstock\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"1555\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/shutterstock_124969421-scaled.jpg?fit=2560%2C1555&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"2560\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">British politician and <a href=\"https://amzn.to/4pbPUfw\">novelist</a> Ann Widdecombe, a former minister of prisons known for <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2011/07/31/stephen-fry-debating-ann-widdecombe-on-the-worth-of-the-catholic-church.html\">her dogmatic conservative views</a>, was found dead Thursday at her home in Devon, England. Long out of parliament and 78 years old, it was initially assumed she had died naturally, but it soon emerged <a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/live/cp9l8l05vxet\">she was beaten to death and that police had arrested a 26 year-old man on suspicion of her murder</a>. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/10/uk-politician-ann-widdecombe-beaten-to-death-in-own-home.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/10/uk-politician-ann-widdecombe-beaten-to-death-in-own-home.html\">UK politician Ann Widdecombe beaten to death in own home</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
